The paper deals with graph theoretical ideas and their application in data mining, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, since the paper specifically focuses on the connectedness of graphs and its application to connected matroids, categories such as cs.DM and cs.GT seem more likely.
